      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 997.1 Carrera S is powered by the 3.8L M97 horizontally-opposed six-cylinder, featuring VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift. The naturally aspirated powerplant is paired with a 6-speed manual transaxle, offering short-throw precision and tactile synchromesh engagement. The chassis benefits from Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM), providing variable damping rates that mitigate body roll while maintaining high-speed stability. Mechanical highlights include four-piston monoblock aluminum calipers over cross-drilled rotors, ensuring consistent thermal management under heavy braking. The engine pulls strongly through the rev range with no signs of bore scoring or IMS issues. While the exterior shows minor road-derived wear, the vehicle\u2019s kinematics, throttle response, and lateral grip remain sharp, making it an ideal candidate for an enthusiast seeking a visceral, analog driving experience.",
